column6: have repeatedly been advised of the foregoing atrocities and conditions and have failed to respond in kind. column9: First Monarch of the Kingdom of EnenKio
column10: Iroijlaplap of the Northern Ratak Atolls of the Marshall Islands
column12: was felt throughout the society.\xc2\xa0 Flags were flown at half mast for a week \nin the Marshalls and for a a month at EnenKio Consulates around the world.\xc2\xa0 His remains were interred in a remote site reserved for the highest ranking chiefs
column13: according to Marshallese custom. \xc2\xa0 His Majesty King Remios Hermios \nSecond Monarch of the Kingdom of EnenKio He was succeeded to the throne by his younger brother
column15: who will formally accept the staff of authority as Second Monarch
column16: titular Head of State of the Kingdom of EnenKio in ceremonies being planned.\xc2\xa0 His \nMajesty Remios Hermios was a retired educator in the Marshalls and maintains a home in the Ratak Atolls. His successor is designated to be his brother

partija srbije predvodjena grupom starih socijalista na celu sa milomirem minicem konacno se odrekla politik herojskog drzanja predsednika te strank slobodana milosevica da jedan slabo obavesten covek ne moze pogotovu ne iz zatvorsk celij upravljati tako velikom partijom kao sto je partija srbije pa zvao se slobodan milosevic'' socijalisti koji za sebe dana kazu da vise nisu slobodana milosevica neprestano u kontaktima sa clanovima te partij pokusavaju da razdvoj odbranu slobodana milosevica u hagu od politickog zivota u srbiji pripisujuci braniocima iz nacionalnog komiteta za milosevica sloboda'' da im je cilj da unist partiju srbije iako je zbog istih takvih gledista socijalista posl predsednika te strank prof branislav ivkov bio iskljucen iz redova sp dana rukovodstvo sp koristi jo teze grublj na racun njihovog predsednika pritom ne strahujuci da bi bilo ko od njih mogao biti iskljucen iz partij ne retko se poslednjih dana u rokovodstvu partij cuje da partija nije slobodan milosev da ne predstvalja tu partiju vec da su partija rukovodstvo glavni odbor te strank medjutim u clanstvu medju te strank stvari se ne odijaju ba po planovima rukovodstva procen idu dotl da se na izborima ocekuj da bata zivojinov osvoji tek number glasova clanovi partij najveci deo njih dana veruj svom heroju slobodanu milosevicu po clanstvu partij ovih dana u rukovodstvu partij oni koji su predsednika te strank pogresno informisali poslednjih godina kada su shvatili da im je odzvonilo'' pokusavaju da sacuvaju sebe predsednika slobodana milosevica mladi socijalisti kojih nema ba mnogo kako se sp hvalio izgleda su na strani predsednika te strank tako se u nastupima na opstinskim odborima mogu cuti uverljivi govori dejana igora raicevica po neki milinka isakovica iz redova mladih socijalista clanova politickog odbora predsednika sp obracanja ovih mladih ljudi medju clanstvom partij imaju deset puta vecu tezuni nego li obracanja politicara koji za sobom vuku teret proslosti stav rukovodstva mladih socijalista se razlikuj od stava saveta mladih koji su takodj na strani predsednika branko ruzic dejan backov najveci branioci zastupnici lika dela slobodana milosevica dana su se pretvorili u njegov najvec kriticar pokusavaju na sve moguc nacin da minorizuju grupu mladih koja ga podrzava cak se poslednjih dana cuje da je najbolji recept da se rukovodstvo mladih odrzi ikao partija srbije predvodjena grupom starih socijalista na celu sa milomirem minicem konacno se odrekla politik herojskog drzanja predsednika te strank slobodana milosevica da jedan slabo obavesten covek ne moze pogotovu ne iz zatvorsk celij upravljati tako velikom partijom kao sto je partija srbije pa zvao se slobodan milosevic'' socijalisti koji za sebe dana kazu da vise nisu slobodana milosevica neprestano u kontaktima sa clanovima te partij pokusavaju da razdvoj odbranu slobodana milosevica u hagu od politickog zivota u srbiji pripisujuci braniocima iz nacionalnog komiteta za milosevica sloboda'' da im je cilj da unist partiju srbije iako je zbog istih takvih gledista socijalista posl predsednika te strank prof branislav ivkov bio iskljucen iz redova sp dana rukovodstvo sp koristi jo teze grublj na racun njihovog predsednika pritom ne strahujuci da bi bilo ko od njih mogao biti iskljucen iz partij ne retko se poslednjih dana u rokovodstvu partij cuje da partija nije slobodan milosev da ne predstvalja tu partiju vec da su partija rukovodstvo glavni odbor te strank medjutim u clanstvu medju te strank stvari se ne odijaju ba po planovima rukovodstva procen idu dotl da se na izborima ocekuj da bata zivojinov osvoji tek number glasova clanovi partij najveci deo njih dana veruj svom heroju slobodanu milosevicu po clanstvu partij ovih dana u rukovodstvu partij oni koji su predsednika te strank pogresno informisali poslednjih godina kada su shvatili da im je odzvonilo'' pokusavaju da sacuvaju sebe predsednika slobodana milosevica mladi socijalisti kojih nema ba mnogo kako se sp hvalio izgleda su na strani predsednika te strank tako se u nastupima na opstinskim odborima mogu cuti uverljivi govori dejana igora raicevica po neki milinka isakovica iz redova mladih socijalista clanova politickog odbora predsednika sp obracanja ovih mladih ljudi medju clanstvom partij imaju deset puta vecu tezuni nego li obracanja politicara koji za sobom vuku teret proslosti stav rukovodstva mladih socijalista se razlikuj od stava saveta mladih koji su takodj na strani predsednika branko ruzic dejan backov najveci branioci zastupnici lika dela slobodana milosevica dana su held onto the hope that their loved ones were just 
missing. It was a place where a child comforted a grieving mother.

At a meeting the public never saw
column3:
the president spoke with several 
hundred of these families in a convention hall.

\x93People said to me
column4: \x91He\x92ll come out. Don\x92t worry
column6: we\x92ll \nsee him soon. I know my loved one
column7: he will - he\x92ll find a place to \nsurvive underneath the rubble and we\x92ll get him out.\x92 I
column8: on the other \nhand had been briefed about the realities
column9: and my job was to hug and \ncry
column10: but I remember the whole time thinking
column11:
\x91This is incredibly sad 
because the loved ones won\x92t come out.\x92\x94

One little boy handed the president a picture of his father in his 
firefighter uniform and as he signed it

and hope. We will work with regional institutions
column3: such as \nthe Summit of the Americas process
column4: the Organization of American States \n(OAS)
column5:
and the Defense Ministerial of the Americas for the benefit of 
the entire hemisphere.

Parts of Latin America confront regional conflict
column6:
especially arising 
from the violence of drug cartels and their accomplices. This conflict 
and unrestrained narcotics trafficking could imperil the health and 
security of the United States. Therefore we have developed an active 
strategy to help the Andean nations adjust their economies
column7: enforce \ntheir laws
column8: defeat terrorist organizations
column9: and cut off the supply of \ndrugs
column10:
while -- as important -- we work to reduce the demand for drugs 
in our own country.

In Colombia
column11:
we recognize the link between terrorist and extremist 
groups that challenge the security of the state and drug trafficking 
activities that help finance the operations of such groups. We are 
working to help Colombia defend its democratic institutions and defeat 
illegal armed groups of both the left and right by extending effective 
sovereignty over the entire national territory and provide basic 
security to the Colombian people.

In Africa
column12: promise and opportunity sit side by side with disease
column14:
and desperate poverty. This threatens both a core value of the United 
States -- preserving human dignity -- and our strategic priority -- 
combating global terror. American interests and American principles
